<objective>
Refactor useFeatureAccess hook from two generic booleans (canManageGuests, canUseWhatsApp) to six granular feature flags (GATE-01 through GATE-06), then update all four consumer files to use the new properties.

Purpose: Enables Phase 5 (Paywalls) to intercept specific actions individually. Also fixes the current over-restrictive behavior where draft users are redirected away from the entire Dashboard -- they should be able to see their guest list.
Output: Working feature gating where draft users see guests + settings, active users see everything.
</objective>

