<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 1: Refactor useFeatureAccess hook to six granular flags</name>
  <files>src/hooks/useFeatureAccess.ts</files>
  <action>
Replace the entire useFeatureAccess hook implementation with the six granular properties per GATE-01 through GATE-06.

Target implementation:
```typescript
import { useEventContext } from '@/contexts/EventContext';
import { useAuth } from '@/contexts/AuthContext';

const FREE_GUEST_LIMIT = 20;

export function useFeatureAccess() {
  const { isActive } = useEventContext();
  const { isSuperAdmin } = useAuth();
  const unlocked = isSuperAdmin || isActive;

  return {
    canAccessSettings:  true as const,      // GATE-01: always open
    canAccessTimeline:  unlocked,            // GATE-02
    canImportGuests:    unlocked,            // GATE-03
    canExportGuests:    unlocked,            // GATE-04
    canSendMessages:    unlocked,            // GATE-05
    maxFreeGuests:      FREE_GUEST_LIMIT,    // GATE-06
  };
}
```

Key points:
- `canAccessSettings` uses `true as const` for type narrowing (always `true`, never `boolean`)
- `FREE_GUEST_LIMIT` is a module-level constant (single source of truth)
- `canManageGuests` and `canUseWhatsApp` are REMOVED entirely (TypeScript will flag all broken consumers)
- Do NOT add enforcement logic for maxFreeGuests -- that belongs to Phase 5 (PAY-04)
  </action>
  <verify>
    <automated>cd C:/dev/github/personal/Wedding-Eyal && npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | head -30</automated>
  </verify>
  <done>useFeatureAccess exports exactly 6 properties: canAccessSettings (true), canAccessTimeline, canImportGuests, canExportGuests, canSendMessages (all boolean), maxFreeGuests (20). Old canManageGuests/canUseWhatsApp properties are gone. TypeScript errors expected in consumers (fixed in Task 2).</done>
</task>

